
[1]contemplation

   CONTEMPLATION, n. [L.]

   1. The act of the mind in considering with attention; meditation;
   study; continued attention of the mind to a particular subject.

   Contemplation is keeping the idea, brought into the mind, some time
   actually in view.

   2. Holy meditation; attention to sacred things; a particular
   application of the foregoing definition.

   To have in contemplation, to intend or purpose, or to have under
   consideration.
